"{\"uid\": \"instyle.com-charlize-theron-sleek-modern-white-mini-dress-pre-olympics-8684272\", \"text\": \"Bright, brilliant and bold.  Getty  The Olympics are in Paris this year-so naturally, they are set to be chicest games in recent memory. Exhibit A: last night, stars turned up for the very stylish Prelude to the Olympics event at Paris' Fondation Louis Vuitton. Amongst them wasCharlize Theron, who was there to co-chair the event alongside Serena Williams, Rosal\\u00eda and Omar S-and Theron certainly set the bar for the kind of crisp, sporty looks we are expecting in Paris for this year's Olympic Games.  The actress wore a bright, bold white mini dress. The asymmetrical one-shoulder shift dress had one strap, which was attached to a dramatic cape shoulder that draped like a waterfall to skim floor. She paired this chic number with delicate accessories: a diamond bracelet, gold strappy heeled sandals, a few dainty diamond rings, and a quilted gold clutch by Christian Dior-she has, of course, been\\u00a0fronting the brand's J'Adore fragrance since 2004 and sheattended their pre-Fall show in April. She completed the sophisticated look with a silver manicure and a low updo with elegant loose waves falling on one side of her face.  Getty  Theron shared a video of her appearance at the event onInstagram, writing, \\\"About last night\\u2026in Paris.\\\"  Zendaya, fresh off the sartorial success of herChallengerspress tour, offered up another sleek and sporty look at the event,wearing a slinky black sequined maxi dress.  Theron may have been the perfect picture of red carpet glamour at last night's pre-Olympics event, but, as the actress has recently revealed, her day-to-day life has been a little more relatable lately. These days, she spends much of her timeraising her two preteen daughters.  Getty  \\\"Oh, my god, they are so embarrassed by me constantly,\\\" she toldE!on the red carpet earlier this month. \\\"They are kids, they are girls, you know? I have a preteen, and I feel like I have a 9-year-old who thinks she's a 13-year-old. It's a lot of girl in our house.\\\"  She added, \\\"I am just trying to keep my head above water because they are smart and they are witty-and they are firecrackers. But they do not go, 'Oh my god, mom, you are so amazing.\\\"  Store and/or access information on a device. Use limited data to select advertising. Create profiles for personalised advertising. Use profiles to select personalised advertising. Create profiles to personalise content. Use profiles to select personalised content. Measure advertising performance. Measure content performance. Understand audiences through statistics or combinations of data from different sources. Develop and improve services. Use limited data to select content.List of Partners (vendors)\"}"